First, go to the given website and look at the rows of buttons or links on the page. In the row just above the bottom one, 
locate the button that allows you to download a file named ciper.txt and download it to your computer. After that, inspect 
the website’s source code by opening the developer tools in your browser and navigate to the CSS files used by the page. 
In the CSS, search for a hidden value that appears as a font-family name; this value contains the encrypted flag. Copy this 
encrypted string. Then open the ciper.txt file you downloaded earlier and find the Python code inside it. 
Use that Python script to decrypt the encrypted string you found in the CSS. Run the script with the encrypted value as the 
input, and the output produced by the script will reveal the decrypted flag.